---
/**
 * ai-evaluation/0001 · Figure 4 — "Two shapes of online eval" (shadow vs A/B,
 * safety vs signal). Copied VERBATIM from the source lesson (figure + svg +
 * figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>); an .astro component for the kebab-case
 * SVG reason.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 240"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Shadow runs the new system on real traffic but discards its output for zero user risk; A/B splits real users so they see the variant and you measure a real outcome signal."
    >
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Two shapes of online eval</text
        >

        <!-- shadow -->
        <rect
            x="30"
            y="40"
            width="270"
            height="160"
            rx="10"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="165" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Shadow</text
        >
        <rect x="50" y="72" width="100" height="26" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="100" y="89" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#111110">live traffic</text>
        <line x1="150" y1="85" x2="172" y2="85" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect x="174" y="72" width="100" height="26" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="224" y="89" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#111110">old &rarr; user</text
        >
        <line
            x1="100"
            y1="98"
            x2="100"
            y2="120"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <rect x="50" y="122" width="100" height="26" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="100" y="139" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#111110">new (parallel)</text
        >
        <text x="200" y="139" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >output discarded</text
        >
        <text
            x="165"
            y="172"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#2f5d3a">zero user risk</text
        >
        <text
            x="165"
            y="187"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#9a2417">no live conversion signal</text
        >

        <!-- A/B -->
        <rect
            x="340"
            y="40"
            width="270"
            height="160"
            rx="10"
            fill="#eef0fb"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="475" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >A/B test</text
        >
        <rect x="430" y="72" width="90" height="24" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#3d54c9"></rect>
        <text x="475" y="88" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#111110">split users</text>
        <line x1="475" y1="96" x2="420" y2="116" stroke="#3d54c9" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
        <line x1="475" y1="96" x2="530" y2="116" stroke="#3d54c9" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
        <rect x="362" y="118" width="116" height="24" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#3d54c9"></rect>
        <text x="420" y="134" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#111110"
            >50% &rarr; old (control)</text
        >
        <rect x="486" y="118" width="116" height="24" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#3d54c9"></rect>
        <text x="544" y="134" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#111110"
            >50% &rarr; new (variant)</text
        >
        <text
            x="475"
            y="172"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#3d54c9">real outcome signal (conversion)</text
        >
        <text
            x="475"
            y="187"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#9a2417">some users see a worse experience</text
        >

        <text x="320" y="226" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Common sequence: shadow first to confirm no regressions &rarr; then A/B to measure the
            real lift.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Shadow buys safety (no user ever sees the new output) but gives no business signal; A/B buys
        a real outcome signal but exposes some users to a possibly-worse variant. Run shadow first,
        then A/B.<sup><a href="#s4" id="r4b">4</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
